        },
        "subject": "LU-4285 kernel: fix unintialized variables in kernel patch",
        "message": "LU-4285 kernel: fix unintialized variables in kernel patch\n\nOne of the SLES base kernel patches leaves local variable un-inited\nin __dquot_initialze().  This can lead to kernel OOPS during common\noperations like mkfs.lustre and mount.\nThis fix alters the kernel patch to init variables properly.\nThe same patch is used for both SP2 and SP3 kernels.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ie6b5a9f8851a5bfbee193b3aa900e4caaf671fa6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
